{"detail":{"ID":2154,"post_author":"1","post_date":"2018-01-09 17:05:28","post_date_gmt":"2018-01-09 17:05:28","post_content":"This post museum artscape building belongs to all the people of Seoul. To best embody this aspiration, it evades authorship, blending instead with the anonymous buildings that surround it in the city and adopting a simple fa\u00e7ade distinguishable only by a generic pattern of rectangular windows. The result is a building with an exterior that is indifferent to difference, aspiring to be like any other building in the city and avoiding an elitist indulgence in design, becoming property shared by all. The project is shaped by concrete urban facts already present in the city: the topography of the land, the geometry of the street, the facade typology of surrounding buildings, the fragmented nature of the site, and, above all, by the open archive as spatial backbone of the building. The open archive extends both horizontally and vertically, connected by stairs and elevators, embodying a topographic interior that allows it to always be near and in symbiotic interaction with all other parts of the program, inviting its exploration with a depth and a symbiosis of functions that is both practical and exciting. This arrangement puts art and visitors first.","post_title":"<p>Pyeongchang Art Complex, Seoul, KR 2017<\/p>","post_excerpt":"","post_status":"publish","comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","post_password":"","post_name":"pyeongchang-art-complex-seoul-kr-2017","to_ping":"","pinged":"","post_modified":"2018-01-10 16:43:07","post_modified_gmt":"2018-01-10 16:43:07","post_content_filtered":"","post_parent":0,"guid":"http:\/\/obra.neptuno.digital\/?post_type=projects&#038;p=2154","menu_order":0,"post_type":"projects","post_mime_type":"","comment_count":"0","filter":"raw","ancestors":[],"page_template":"","post_category":[],"tags_input":[],"extended":{"year":"","images":[{"image":{"width":1500,"height":927,"file":"2018\/01\/OBRA_PYEONG